	<TextInfo>
		<Text Type="Business Summary" lastModified="2015-09-14T07:14:02">Anglo American PLC (Anglo American) is a mining company. The Company's segments include Iron Ore and Manganese, which includes iron ore, manganese ore and alloys; Coal, which includes metallurgical coal and thermal coal; Copper, which includes copper; Nickel, which includes nickel; Niobium, which includes niobium; Phosphates, which includes phosphates; Platinum, which includes platinum group metals, and De Beers, which includes rough and polished diamonds. Its portfolio offers bulk commodities and base metals to precious metals and diamonds (through De Beers). Its bulk commodities include iron ore, manganese, metallurgical coal and thermal coal. The Company's base metals and minerals include copper, nickel, niobium and phosphates. In precious metals and minerals, the Company produces both platinum and diamonds. Its mining operations, projects and exploration and marketing activities extend across southern Africa, South America, Australia, North America, Asia and Europe.</Text>
		<Text Type="Financial Summary" lastModified="2015-10-09T13:41:41">BRIEF: For the six months ended 30 June 2015, Anglo American plc revenues decreased 19% to $11.56B. Net loss totaled $3.02B vs. income of $1.46B. Revenues reflect Iron Ore &amp; Managanese segment decrease of 30% to $2.01B, De Beers Investments segment decrease of 21% to $3.02B, Europe segment decrease of 28% to $1.87B, Japan segment decrease of 30% to $1.27B, Diamond Production (Carats) decrease of 3% to 15.6M carats.</Text>
